{"word":"ἁλμυρός","slug":"ἁλμυρός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἁλμυρός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἅλμη'><el>ἅλμη</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>salt, briny</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of taste, <i>salt, brackish</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>bitter, distasteful</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>amarus</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>ἁλμυρὰ κλαίειν</el> to weep <i>bitterly</i>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}